@RequestParam vs @RequestBody
1.@RequestParam
Use it when you need one or a few simple values.
Client sends:

GET /customers?id=5

The URL contains:

id=5

Controller:

@GetMapping("/customers")
public Customer getCustomer(@RequestParam Long id) {
    return customerService.getCustomer(id);
}
What happens?

Spring reads:

id = 5

and puts it into:

Long id
