e tiny addition worth knowing: @RequestParam isn't limited to GET requests — you can use it with POST/PUT too (it just reads from the URL query string regardless of HTTP method). But your instinct is right: in practice, @RequestParam is most commonly paired with GET (simple lookups), and @RequestBody with POST/PUT (sending structured data).